# Theme Toggle — Light/Dark + Color Themes

Add a premium theme system with a **quick light/dark toggle** and a **color theme dropdown** offering 6 curated palettes. Themes persist in `localStorage` and apply instantly via CSS custom properties on the `<html>` element.

## Proposed Changes

### Theme Infrastructure

#### [NEW] [ThemeContext.jsx](file:///c:/AppDev/Surgical_Procedure_Listings_App/frontend/src/context/ThemeContext.jsx)

React context providing:
- `theme` — current color theme key (`indigo`, `ocean`, `sunset`, `forest`, `rose`, `slate`)
- `mode` — `light` or `dark`
- `setTheme(key)` / `toggleMode()` — setters
- On mount: reads from `localStorage`, sets `data-theme` and `data-mode` attributes on `<html>`
- On change: writes to `localStorage`, updates `<html>` attributes

#### [NEW] [ThemeToggle.jsx](file:///c:/AppDev/Surgical_Procedure_Listings_App/frontend/src/components/ThemeToggle.jsx)

A polished header widget with two parts:
1. **Sun/Moon icon button** — instant light ↔ dark toggle with smooth rotation animation
2. **Palette dropdown** — shows color swatches for each theme; click to select, with a checkmark on the active theme

Dropdown uses `lucide-react` icons (`Sun`, `Moon`, `Palette`, `Check`, `ChevronDown`). Closes on outside click.

---

### CSS Theme Definitions

#### [MODIFY] [index.css](file:///c:/AppDev/Surgical_Procedure_Listings_App/frontend/src/index.css)

Define CSS custom properties under `[data-theme][data-mode]` selectors. Each combination (6 themes × 2 modes = 12 variants) sets variables like:

```
--bg-primary, --bg-secondary, --bg-card
--text-primary, --text-secondary, --text-muted
--accent, --accent-light, --accent-dark, --accent-bg
--border, --border-accent
--shadow-color
```

Default = `[data-theme="indigo"][data-mode="light"]` matching the current look.  All 12 variants will be exhaustively defined so switching themes is seamless.

---

### Component Updates

#### [MODIFY] [App.jsx](file:///c:/AppDev/Surgical_Procedure_Listings_App/frontend/src/App.jsx)

- Import `ThemeProvider` and wrap the return in `<ThemeProvider>`
- Add `<ThemeToggle />` in the header (right side)
- Replace hardcoded color classes with CSS variable equivalents via inline `style` + utility classes that reference `var(--*)`.  E.g. `bg-gray-50` → `style={{ backgroundColor: 'var(--bg-primary)' }}`.

#### [MODIFY] [SearchInput.jsx](file:///c:/AppDev/Surgical_Procedure_Listings_App/frontend/src/components/SearchInput.jsx)

Update input background, border, text, and icon colors to use CSS variables.

#### [MODIFY] [DualCodeDisplay.jsx](file:///c:/AppDev/Surgical_Procedure_Listings_App/frontend/src/components/DualCodeDisplay.jsx)

Update card backgrounds, header bands, text colors, and border colors to use CSS variables.

#### [MODIFY] [AuthorizedProcedures.jsx](file:///c:/AppDev/Surgical_Procedure_Listings_App/frontend/src/components/AuthorizedProcedures.jsx)

Update card backgrounds, hover states, text, and badge colors to use CSS variables.

#### [MODIFY] [main.jsx](file:///c:/AppDev/Surgical_Procedure_Listings_App/frontend/src/main.jsx)

No changes needed — the `ThemeProvider` wraps inside [App.jsx](file:///c:/AppDev/Surgical_Procedure_Listings_App/frontend/src/App.jsx).

